{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsRx2cDXnoWGYPERAZk6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Restore complete. Summary:\n\n- **Root cause**: `rabbitmq-0`'s data PVC was wiped; the StatefulSet was scaled to 0 with a backup tarball (`rabbitmq-0.tgz`, containing rabbitmq-0's full mnesia directory) sitting on the `rabbitmq-backup` PVC, and a fresh empty `data-rabbitmq-0` PVC.\n- **Fix**: Created a one-off restore `Job` (native Job, no CRDs/operators) that mounted both PVCs, extracted the tarball into `data-rabbitmq-0` at the correct `mnesia/...` path, fixed ownership to `rabbitmq:rabbitmq`, and ran `rabbitmqctl force_boot` — necessary because rabbitmq-0's restored mnesia data still remembers it was part of a 3-node cluster, and without `force_boot` it would block waiting for peers (deadlocking the StatefulSet's ordered rollout).\n- Scaled the `rabbitmq` StatefulSet back to 3 replicas. `rabbitmq-0` booted standalone via the forced boot, then `rabbitmq-1` and `rabbitmq-2` (fresh PVCs) auto-joined via the existing `rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s` plugin — all native, no data loss.\n\nVerified:\n- All 3 nodes (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) are `Running`, clustered, no network partitions.\n- `/app` vhost contains `app-backup`, type `classic`, with **20 messages** restored.\n\nNote: `app-producer` is still CrashLoopBackOff (unrelated to this stage's goal, which only covers cluster/queue restoration) — leaving it as-is since it wasn't part of this stage's scope."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":495,"cache_read_input_tokens":76701,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":495},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66b6b091-f3c0-4615-bfa4-94b24beafe38","uuid":"4a2a1b24-bf2c-4a85-a24d-